18
00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:05.710
In recent years, they've seen 50 and
60,000 applicants.

19
00:01:05.710 --> 00:01:10.940
This leads to a funneled process,
where they vet the CDs, the resumes at one

20
00:01:10.940 --> 00:01:14.560
stage, they invite some of those to do a
phone interview, they invite some of those

21
00:01:14.560 --> 00:01:18.350
on site to do a face to face interview,
and then they hire some subset of those.

22
00:01:18.350 --> 00:01:21.393
By looking rigorously at who
makes it through the process and

23
00:01:21.393 --> 00:01:25.149
how good their assessments are in
comparison to what actually happens down

24
00:01:25.149 --> 00:01:28.382
the road, they've been able to
optimize this hiring process.

25
00:01:28.382 --> 00:01:32.855
They're much more efficient now
about bringing the right number from

26
00:01:32.855 --> 00:01:36.190
the resume level to
the phone interview level.

27
00:01:36.190 --> 00:01:39.720
And then the right percentage
of those to the on site,

28
00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:44.550
allowing them to make better decisions and
use their resources more efficiently.

29
00:01:44.550 --> 00:01:46.480
Another example is a little
